            "description": "",
            "details": "<p class=\"p1\"><em>Enbār</em>: It lies in the <em>vilāyet-i ‘Irāḳ</em> (province of Iraq), located on the bank of the <em>Furāt</em> (Euphrates River). The first of the <em>Ḫulefā-yı ‘Abbāsiyye</em> (Abbasid caliphs)—<em>Seffāḥ</em> (al-Saffāḥ)—resided there. There is also a village named <em>Enbār</em> in the vilāyet of <em>Cürcān</em> (Gurgān). <em>Ebü’l-Ḥasen ‘Alī Enbārī</em> is named in relation to that village. [translation]</p>",
            "end": 1599,
